AGI - Seven humanitarian workers, including some foreigners, were killed in an Israeli attack on Deir el-Balah> in the Gaza Strip. Among the victims are Polish, Australian and British citizens. In the attack, which hit the car on which the co-workers traveled, at least one Palestinian was killed. Another victim had double citizenship, of Usa and Canada. It is believed that they are the first foreign humanitarian workers to be killed in Gaza since the beginning of the war.&nbsp; The NGO, which together with the Spanish Open Arms brought the first shipment of aid from the sea to Gaza City, announced that it had suspended humanitarian operations.
&nbsp;
World Central Kitchen, the U.S.-based humanitarian organization, confirmed that several people were killed in the attack, reported the founder and leader of the group, the famous chef Jose Andres.&nbsp;> The organization "has lost many of our brothers and sisters in an IDF air strike in Gaza. I am sore and grieved for their families and friends and all our family" Andres said about X. "They are not faceless people... I'm not without a name. The Israeli government must stop this indiscriminate killing. He must stop limiting humanitarian aid, stop killing civilians and humanitarian workers, and stop using food as a weapon."&nbsp;
