Israel: tragic accident
On the death of 5 humanitarian workers in Gaza, including 4 Westerners, the IDF states that it is "executing a thorough examination at the highest levels to understand the circumstances of this tragic incident". The Army adds that "it is making great efforts to ensure safe delivery of humanitarian aid and has worked closely with the World Central Kitchen in its efforts to provide food and humanitarian aid to Gaza residents."
&nbsp;
<h2> It will be an independent authority to investigate the attack
It will be an organism of independent experts >, the Mechanism of investigation and evaluation of the Facts, to investigate the attack > The Israeli army told him. The Israeli Defense Force spokesman, Daniel Hagari, added in a message that he personally spoke to chef Andres, to express his condolences for the death of workers. "We will open an investigation to examine this serious incident. This will help us reduce the risk that such an event is repeated."
&nbsp;
<h2> Poland calls the ambassador of Israel
The Israeli diplomatic representative in Poland was summoned by Warsaw. The Polish Foreign Minister asked the ambassador for urgent deployments. Reuters agency reports it. "I personally asked the Israeli ambassador Yacov Livne," wrote Polish minister Radoslaw Sikorski on the social platform. "He assured me that Poland will soon receive the results of the investigations on this tragedy. I join my condolences with the family of our brave volunteer and all civilian victims in the Gaza Strip."
&nbsp;
<h2>Netanyahu admits, unintentionally affected co-operators
&nbsp; Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu admitted that the Israeli army "involuntarily" killed the seven humanitarian workers of the World Central Kitchen (Wck) who died in a raid in the Gaza Strip.<br> "Unfortunately, in recent days a tragic case occurred in which our forces unintentionally hit innocent people in the Gaza Strip". The Prime Minister, already resigned, reiterated that the incident will be investigated in detail and justified by saying that things like this " happen in war". "We will do everything we can to prevent this from happening again," he said. Shortly before, the Israeli army announced that an independent military entity, the Fact-Finding and Assessment Mechanism, will investigate the attack, which today led the NGO Wck to suspend its operations in the region.&nbsp;

